# Repository Language Policy

- Write all repository content in English, including code, comments, documentation, rules, skills, prompts, commit messages, and configuration text.
- Do not add non-English text to files in this repository unless the user explicitly asks for localized content as the deliverable.
- Reply to the user in the same language they use when they address the agent.
- When Plan Mode is active, present chat plans in the same language the user used to ask for the work.
- When saving Plan Mode output or approved plans into repository files, translate them to English unless the user explicitly requests localized repository content.
- Keep examples, identifiers, and inline comments in repository files in English.
